<h2>From the command line</h2>
<p>
  <code>whatcable-cli.exe</code> prints a JSON snapshot of every USB-C port, the power
  adapter, the Thunderbolt chain, and connected displays. The <code>video</code> and
  <code>thunderbolt</code> sections are Windows-only additions; pass <code>--legacy</code>
  to drop them for tools that still consume the macOS schema.
</p>
<pre><code><span class="prompt">&gt;</span> whatcable-cli snapshot
<span class="comment"># macOS-compatible schema only:</span>
<span class="prompt">&gt;</span> whatcable-cli snapshot --legacy
<span class="comment"># pipe into jq:</span>
<span class="prompt">&gt;</span> whatcable-cli snapshot | jq .ports[0].dataLink</code></pre>
